docs/TEST_GATES.md:276:Long-running workflows must not leave the user guessing whether copy-and-paste is required. A run may claim no-copy completion only when its final summary includes `REMOTE_EVIDENCE: PASS` and the relevant terminal log or command-run report has been committed and pushed. If that proof is unavailable, the final summary must say that remote evidence is incomplete and paste-output is required.
docs/TEST_GATES.md:288:Every relevant terminal work block must end with a machine-readable SUMMARY block containing WORK RESULT, EVIDENCE RESULT, OVERALL RESULT, REMOTE_EVIDENCE, terminal_log, command_report, NEXT_CHAT_REPLY, and the final result marker.
docs/TEST_GATES.md:290:A final `### RESULT: PASS ###` is valid only when `WORK RESULT: PASS`, `OVERALL RESULT: PASS`, and, for relevant workflows, `REMOTE_EVIDENCE: PASS` are all true. A previous inner FAIL must not be converted into a final PASS by a later commit or push of evidence. Evidence success and work success are separate outcomes.
docs/TEST_GATES.md:321:- Final summary contract: relevant workflow blocks must end with the framed SUMMARY contract containing WORK RESULT, EVIDENCE RESULT, OVERALL RESULT, REMOTE_EVIDENCE, terminal_log, command_report, NEXT_CHAT_REPLY, and final result marker.
docs/STATUS.md:93:The no-copy/evidence workflow now requires a mandatory final SUMMARY block for relevant terminal work. `WORK RESULT`, `EVIDENCE RESULT`, `OVERALL RESULT`, `REMOTE_EVIDENCE`, `terminal_log`, `command_report`, and `NEXT_CHAT_REPLY` must be reported separately. A final PASS requires work success and evidence success; a pushed log can prove a failure without turning that failure into success.
docs/STATUS.md:120:- Final summary contract: relevant workflow blocks must end with the framed SUMMARY contract containing WORK RESULT, EVIDENCE RESULT, OVERALL RESULT, REMOTE_EVIDENCE, terminal_log, command_report, NEXT_CHAT_REPLY, and final result marker.
docs/governance/FINAL_SUMMARY_CONTRACT.md:3:Every relevant workflow block must end with the framed SUMMARY contract. This contract is durable and must not disappear across chats, handoffs, or command-generation paths.
docs/governance/FINAL_SUMMARY_CONTRACT.md:10:WORK RESULT: PASS|FAIL|PENDING|HARD-FAIL|NO-COMMAND
docs/governance/FINAL_SUMMARY_CONTRACT.md:13:REMOTE_EVIDENCE: PASS|FAIL|PARTIAL|NOT_REQUIRED
docs/governance/FINAL_SUMMARY_CONTRACT.md:16:NEXT_CHAT_REPLY: p|paste-output|ask-agent-to-queue-command|continue|stop
docs/governance/FINAL_SUMMARY_CONTRACT.md:21:This is the preferred end marker for agent-directed terminal blocks, remote command reports, release work, merge verification, and handoff-sensitive work. Short local experiments may use a smaller marker, but any state-changing or evidence-bearing workflow must use the framed SUMMARY.
